FT  01 AUG 92 / Markets: At a Glance - Actuaries offer advice service
Chantrey Financial Services and Wolanski &amp; Co., the consulting actuaries,
are offering a fee-based advice service for trustees and managers of final
salary pension schemes. This is aimed particularly at those who have been
made redundant, or are leaving for other reasons. The service will include
an explanation of retained benefits, a concise explanation of the options
available, and an opinion on whether a transfer would be in the member's
best interests. The fee is Pounds 250 plus VAT per report per pension scheme
member, and retainer fees are also possible.
